Title: Show Your Work!: 10 Ways to Share Your Creativity and Get Discovered
Author: Austin Kleon
My Review: This book has been on my reading list for a long time, and I finally read it. In my view, the best books motivate you to do something you never thought of before or thought you couldn't do, and this book did just that. While reading this book, I decided to show more work on LinkedIn, even if it is not perfect. I also realized that I should finish my site soon, rent a server, buy a unique domain name, and publish articles and videos.

My Review: Reading "How to Be Interesting" is uninteresting, just like a nerd who wants to act positive and humanily. But I have to say, I enjoy it, and it is a picture book for adults. There are interesting pictures and short ideas, I learnt a lot of short expressions. And the most important point is it is so short, I finished it in a few hours. I think it is a beginning-level material for non-native speakers to practise reading.

Title: Cici's Journal: The Adventures of a Writer-In-Training
Author: Joris Chamblain
My Review:
最近不知道什么人在瞎传说《Cici‘s journal》这本书是雅思单词书之类的，说的有鼻子有眼的。刚好图书馆就有，当天就借来看了下。我虽然没考过雅思（背过一段时间的王陆的单词书）但是也知道这不可能是雅思级别的词汇好么！

但是这本漫画书还是挺好看的。分为上下2个故事，我喜欢第一个故事里的瑰丽想象，但更喜欢第二个故事里的爱与成长。

而且这本书的排版和设计都很可爱，喜欢那种手写的字体，但是漫画对话全部都是大写字母真的看得我很累，主要还是不习惯吧
